
🔗 Connecting Lambda to Bedrock Agent using Action Groups

📌 Overview

In this step, we connect the AWS Lambda function to the Amazon Bedrock Agent using an Action Group.

An Action Group enables the AI agent to:

Execute external tools (like Lambda functions)

Perform real AWS operations

Move beyond just generating text responses



❓ Why Action Groups Are Needed

A Bedrock Agent alone can:

Understand user queries

Generate intelligent responses

However, it cannot directly interact with AWS services.

To perform real operations such as:

Discovering AWS resources

Deleting unused resources

Running automation tasks

👉 The agent must use Action Groups, which act as a bridge between:

AI Agent 🧠

AWS Services ⚙️ (via Lambda)




🪜 Steps to Add Lambda Function to the Agent


Step 1: Open Bedrock Console

Navigate to Amazon Bedrock → Agents


Step 2: Select Your Agent

Choose your agent:
Ritik-AWS-Admin-Agent


Step 3: Open Agent Builder

Click Edit in Agent Builder



Step 4: Create Action Group

Scroll to Action Groups

Click Add

Fill the details:

Action Group Name:
cost-cleanup-tools

Action Group Type:
Define with function details



Step 5: Configure Lambda Invocation

Select: Use existing Lambda function

Choose:
BedrockCostAgentTools



⚙️ Define Functions for the Agent

Inside the Action Group, we define the functions the agent can call.



🔍 Function 1: Discover Resources

Function Name:
discover_cost_resources

Confirmation Required:
❌ Disabled

Parameters:
Name	Type	Required	Description
Region	String	No	AWS region to scan (default: ap-south-1)
🗑️ Function 2: Delete Resources

Function Name:
delete_cost_resource

Description:
Always call using a single JSON object containing resource_type, resource_id, region, and confirm_token.

Confirmation Required:
❌ Disabled

Parameters:
Name	Type	Required	Description
confirm_token	String	Yes	Must be CONFIRM to execute deletion
resource_type	String	Yes	EBS_SNAPSHOT, EBS_VOLUME, EIP, EC2_INSTANCE
resource_id	String	Yes	Resource ID (vol-xxx, snap-xxx, etc.)
region	String	Yes	AWS region (default: ap-south-1)


💾 Step 6: Save Configuration

Click Save & Exit



🚀 Step 7: Prepare the Agent

In the Test panel (right side)


Click Prepare

👉 This step applies all configurations and enables the agent for testing

✅ Result of This Step



After completing this setup:

✅ Bedrock Agent is connected to Lambda

✅ Agent can discover AWS resources

✅ Agent can delete resources safely (with confirmation)

✅ Real AWS operations are now enabled



🧠 Key Insight

Action Groups transform your AI agent from a chatbot into an intelligent AWS operator
